      "message": "[Major] Line 13: The regeneration script hard-codes `--minimum-deployment-target 13.0`, which can produce an `Assets.car` that is not aligned with the app\u0027s actual CMake deployment target. If the project still supports older macOS versions, this risks shipping an asset catalog compiled for a newer minimum than the binary itself. Pass the deployment target in explicitly or default it from the environment/CMake docs, e.g.:\n```suggestion\nMIN_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET\u003d\"${MACOSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET:-${CMAKE_OSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET:-10.15}}\"\n\nxcrun actool AppIcon.icon --compile . --app-icon AppIcon \\\n  --include-all-app-icons --enable-on-demand-resources NO \\\n  --target-device mac --platform macosx \\\n  --minimum-deployment-target \"${MIN_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET}\" \\\n  --output-partial-info-plist \"${PARTIAL_PLIST}\"\n```",
